-- Pork Prices in China Increase 7.1% in July From Month Earlier, NDRC Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-08-02T01:46:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/china-s-pork-prices-jumped-7-1-in-july-corn-wheat-advanced-ndrc-says.html

          
          
             China’s pork prices jumped 7.1
percent on on average in July compared with the previous month,
the National Development and Reform Commission said today.
China’s wheat prices gained 1.2 percent and corn prices advanced
2 percent, the commission said in a separate statement on its
website. The changes were based on surveys of 36 major cities
across China, it said.  
          
          


  


        